# WANTED engine — ESP-IDF host-edge glue.
#
# Engine values live in the engine's own Kconfig; only edges into ESP-IDF's
# symbols belong here. A CONFIG_WANTED_* symbol declared here would shadow the
# engine's and give the build two answers for one question.

menu "WANTED engine"

config WANTED_ESP_TLS
    bool "TLS secure sockets (mbedTLS)"
    default n
    select MBEDTLS_TLS_ENABLED
    help
        Back the engine's secure socket types (tcps://, udps://) with the
        mbedTLS stack ESP-IDF ships, and build with SECURE_SOCKETS=1. Mirrors
        the NuttX app's SYSTEM_WANTED_TLS. Without it secure socket entries are
        rejected at wapp launch.

endmenu
